This paper is about training agents to communicate with each other in an interactive world, which falls under the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of a new model and training algorithm, which involves learning representations from raw pixels, which is related to computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of metrics to measure the effectiveness of the communication, which is related to natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of agents in an interactive world, which is related to robotics (cs.RO).
